               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                    <locus from="1ra" to="6rb"/>
                    <locus from="9ra" to="17rb"/>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1489Gadlas">Gadla Ṣādǝqān za-Bāraknāhā</title>
                     <incipit>
                       <locus target="#1ra"/>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez"/>
                        <supplied reason="undefined" resp="DN">እም</supplied>ረኃብ፡ ውስተ፡
                         <supplied reason="lost" resp="DN">ጸጋብ፡</supplied> ወእምጻማ፡
                         ውስተ፡ <supplied reason="undefined" resp="DN">እ</supplied>ረፍት፡ ወእምሕማም፡ ውስተ፡
                         <supplied reason="undefined" resp="DN">ጥዒና፡</supplied> ኀበ፡ አስተ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="DN">ዳለወ፡ እግ</supplied>
                         ዚአብሔር፡ ለአ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="DN">ለ፡</supplied><gap reason="lost"/>ያፈቅርዎ፡
                        </incipit>
                     <note>Due to the misplaced leaves, this beginning corresponds to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XELQF66E"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi"/><title level="m">Ricordi di un soggiorno in Eritrea</title><author><forename>Carlo</forename><surname>Conti Rossini</surname></author><pubPlace>Asmara</pubPlace><publisher>Istituto per l'Oriente</publisher><date>1903</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note></note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note><citedRange unit="page">16</citedRange></bibl>. The leaf<locus target="#9ra"/>
                     contains the actual incipit of the work,
                     <foreign xml:lang="gez"><supplied reason="lost" resp="DN">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩
                     አምላ</supplied>ክ፡ ዝውእቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ገድሎሙ፡ ለጻድቃን፡ <gap reason="lost"/>መዋእሊሁ፡ ለአ<supplied reason="lost"/>ልሜድ፡
                   ንጕሰ፡ ኢትዮጵያ።</foreign>. The text on <locus target="#17vb"/> ends with words immadiately preceeding
                   that on <locus target="#1ra"/>, <forename xml:lang="gez">ተፈሥሑ᎓ እስመ᎓ አምሰጡ፡</forename>
                   (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XELQF66E"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi"/><title level="m">Ricordi di un soggiorno in Eritrea</title><author><forename>Carlo</forename><surname>Conti Rossini</surname></author><pubPlace>Asmara</pubPlace><publisher>Istituto per l'Oriente</publisher><date>1903</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note></note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note><citedRange unit="page">16</citedRange></bibl>).
                    The text of the Vita seems to be quite similar to the one published in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XELQF66E"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi"/><title level="m">Ricordi di un soggiorno in Eritrea</title><author><forename>Carlo</forename><surname>Conti Rossini</surname></author><pubPlace>Asmara</pubPlace><publisher>Istituto per l'Oriente</publisher><date>1903</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note></note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note><citedRange unit="page">7-22</citedRange></bibl>, but slightly shorter, the end (<foreign xml:lang="gez">እስከ᎓ ይገንዩ᎓ ፀር᎓ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡</foreign>) corresponding
                          to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XELQF66E"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi"/><title level="m">Ricordi di un soggiorno in Eritrea</title><author><forename>Carlo</forename><surname>Conti Rossini</surname></author><pubPlace>Asmara</pubPlace><publisher>Istituto per l'Oriente</publisher><date>1903</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note></note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note><citedRange unit="page">21</citedRange></bibl>.
                           The rest of the edited text is missing in (the passages in
                            <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XELQF66E"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi"/><title level="m">Ricordi di un soggiorno in Eritrea</title><author><forename>Carlo</forename><surname>Conti Rossini</surname></author><pubPlace>Asmara</pubPlace><publisher>Istituto per l'Oriente</publisher><date>1903</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note></note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1903Ricordi</note><citedRange unit="page">21-22</citedRange></bibl>
                            that start with <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስምዑኬ᎓ እንግርክሙ᎓ ሀለወት᎓ ምድር᎓</foreign> and
                            <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንግባእኬ᎓ ኀበ᎓ ክብራ᎓ ለመጠራ᎓</foreign>).
                            Besides, the Vita differs from the edited text in that it is styled
                            as the “Vita of the Righteous Ones of Dabra Maʿṣo” in <ref target="#coloph1"/>.
                            In a couple of passages the name <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0919Baraknaha">Bāraknāhā</placeName> has been substituted to for
                            <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0039MY">Dabra Maʿṣo</placeName> (see <locus target="12vb">fol. 12 vb</locus>, l.17, with other slight changes;
                            (unreadable but unlikely <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0919Baraknaha">Bāraknāhā</placeName> on <locus target="1rb">fol. 1rb</locus>, l.4; however,
                            <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0919Baraknaha">Bāraknāhā</placeName> has been
                            left unchanged in <locus target="#9vb">fol. 9vb</locus>, l.1).
                   </note>

                   <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                      <locus from="6ra" to="6rb" cert="medium"/>ዛ<add place="above">ቲ፡</add> መጽሐፍ፡ ተፈጸመ፡ ገ<add place="above">ድ</add>ሎሙ፡
                      ለጻድቃን፨ ዘደብረ፡ ማ<add place="above">ዕ</add>ጾ፨ ዘአልቦሙ፡ ኍልቈ፡ በረ<add place="above">ከ</add>ተ፡ ፀሎቶሙ፡ ወሐብተ፡ ረድኤቶሙ፡ ለኵሎሙ፡ ጻድቃን፨ ምስሌሆሙ፡ ይደምረነ፡ <add place="above">ወይምሀረነ</add>፡ ኢየሱስ፡
                      ክርስቶስ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሮሙ፡ እቍበ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወለጸሓፊ፡ <gap reason="lost" resp="DN"/><cb n="b"/>
                   </colophon>
                   <note>
                   The colophon mentions the commissioner <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13554EqwebaMikael">ʾƎqʷǝba Mikāʾel</persName>
                    and the scribe whose name is cannot be
                   read. The biggest part of the colophon is unreadable
                   (only a few words can be discerned on <locus target="#6rb"/>).
                   </note>
                  </msItem>


                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                    <locus from="6rb" to="8vb"/>
                    <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6176MalkaSadeqanB">Malkǝʾa Ṣādǝqān za-Bāraknāhā</title>
                    <incipit>
                    <locus target="#6rb"/>
                     <foreign xml:lang="gez"/>
                     <gap reason="lost" resp="DN"/>ዝክረ፡ ው<gap reason="lost" resp="DN"/>
                     ያንቅሐኒ፡ ወያንስአኒ፡ እምንዋመ፡ ሐኬት፡ ማህጐሊ፡ <sic resp="DN">ጰራሊጦስ፡</sic>
                     ስቴ፡ <sic resp="DN">ሕና፡</sic> መቀላሊ፡
                     </incipit>
                      <note>The incipit of the text and
                        some further text passages are not readable due to the condition of the manuscript.
                        The text ends on <locus target="8vb"/> with <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዘኢይደልዎ፡
                      ለዓለም፡ በስጋ፡ ዘረከቡ</foreign> (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/RSA6WCVU"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Raineri1980Sadqan"/><title level="a">Vita dei giusti: missionari dell'Etiopia nel sesto secolo: varianti e inno</title><title level="j">Ephemerides Carmeliticae</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Osvaldo</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Raineri</t:surname></author><date>1980</date><biblScope unit="volume">31</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">2</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">377-413</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">393</citedRange></bibl>, which is stanza 23 out of 32 in the edition.
                      The rest is missing.</note>
                  </msItem>

